Document: VisualShaderNodeVectorRefract
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodevectorrefract.rst
Summary: Represents the refract function in shader language, calculating refraction based on incident vector, normal vector, and refraction ratio.

Description
Translated to `refract(I, N, eta)` in the shader language, where `I` is the incident vector, `N` is the normal vector and `eta` is the ratio of the indices of the refraction.